The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, April 10: The Reserve Bank of India has provided banks a breather by revising the method of calculating the current value of restructured loans. The (existing) formula has resulted in higher provisioning due to a rise in the rate of interest during the last few years. It has been decided to modify the formula for computing diminution in the fair value of a restructured loan, the central bank said in a notification.                             
	 New Delhi, April 10: The Foreign Investment Promotion Board has deferred a decision on Vodafone Essars proposal to hive off its tower businesses into a separate company as the home ministry is understood to have sought more time to examine it.                             
	 New Delhi, April 10: The National Pharmaceutical Pricing Authority (NPPA) has asked enforcement agencies to recover around Rs 116 crore from 31 pharmaceutical firms, including Dr Reddys Laboratories, Alkem, Cadila Healthcare and Wyeth, for overcharging.                            
	 New Delhi, April 10: The number of policies issued by life insurance companies in the country was down 0.1 per cent in the first 11 months of 2008-09, with insurance major LIC registering a dip of 6 per cent.                             
	 New Delhi, April 10: The National Highways Authority of India (NHAI) is set to raise Rs 3,000 crore this fiscal through tax-free bonds to fund various projects.                                                                                                                           
